{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JscFMW2Tthpr8iaBtoP6YJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 fake OCR recipe text files with very specific requirements:\n\n1. Save to `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.22.txt`\n2. Filename rules:\n   - SPACES not hyphens/underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match text content title\n\n3. Mix: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n\n4. Recipe types: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n\n5. Avoid these existing recipes:\n   - ARAYES SHRAK\n   - Smażona zielona fasolka\n   - CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\n   - SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\n   - MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD\n   - LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS\n   - Baked Eggs with Feta\n   - Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\n   - Faszerowana papryka\n   - OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH\n   - FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS\n   - KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA\n   - Obwarzanek Warszawski\n   - Tomato Basil Pasta\n   - Lemon Herb Grilled Chicken\n   - Roasted Garlic Broccoli\n   - Placki Ziemniaczane\n   - Chocolate Chip Cookies\n   - Żurek\n   - Berry Tart\n   - Beet and Goat Cheese Salad\n   - Kielbasa z Cebulą\n\n6. Pattern requirements:\n   - 5 files with SPILLOVER (40-60 lines): Start with 10-50 lines of corrupted text from previous recipe, then actual title. \n   - 3 files with NARRATIVE (15-60 lines): 3-7 lines of prose intro between title and ingredients\n   - 2 files with SIMPLE (15-60 lines): Basic OCR noise, stray numbers, page headers, broken words\n\nI need to generate 10 recipes mixing English and Polish. For the English recipes, I'm thinking: Spinach and Ricotta Pie, Baked Cod with Herbs, Carrot and Ginger Soup, Peach Cobbler, Garlic Mushroom Risotto, and one more. For Polish recipes, I'll create titles with proper diacritics. I'll distribute these across the three pattern types—5 spillover files with garbled text fragments preceding the actual recipe, 3 narrative files with introductory prose, and 2 simple files with basic OCR errors and noise. teaspoon vanilla extract and salt. Mix the flour with water until smooth, then fold into the prepared pan and bake at 225°C for 45-50 minutes until golden. The stray text fragments mention serving warm with cream and storing in an airtight container for up to 5 days. Now moving into the actual Spinach and Ricotta Pie recipe with fresh spinach, ricotta cheese, Parmesan, eggs, and puff pastry as the base ingredients.\n\nFor the spinach pie, I need to preheat the oven to 375°F, clean and chop the spinach, then sauté it until wilted. The ricotta, Parmesan, and eggs get mixed with the cooked spinach and seasoned with salt, pepper, and nutmeg. Spread this mixture onto the puff pastry sheet and bake for 35-40 minutes until the top turns golden.\n\nNow I'm planning to create 10 recipe files with varying OCR authenticity levels. The list includes spinach and ricotta pie, baked cod with herbs, carrot and ginger soup, peach cobbler, garlic mushroom risotto, herb crusted lamb chops, and several Polish dishes like bigos, kluski, chleb żytni, and zupa koperkowa. Each will be tagged with a format type—spillover, narrative, or simple—to indicate the OCR quality level I'll simulate.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":75263,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":75263},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8392c7b6-a894-479d-8452-f4cbd3d27103","uuid":"461e684e-b91b-4a99-a42a-05597d7bb42f"}
