{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JscFMW2Tthpr8iaBtoP6YJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VkoY9UjJRnkoXZsRvv7sPw","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Spinach and Ricotta Pie.generated.22.txt","content":"[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER FROM PREVIOUS PAGE]\nınstructions:\nHeat the oil to 180°C until shimmering. Carefully lower the dough\nballs into the hot oil and fry for 2-3 minutes per side until\nthey are golden brown and puffy. Remove with a slotted spoon and\ndrain on paper towels sprinkled with powdered sugar.\n\nServe warm with a drizzle of honey and finely ground pistachios.\nStore in an airtight contaıner for up to 3 days - reheat ın a\nwarm oven before serving.\n\nPage 34 | Middle Eastern Breads & Pastries\n\nOptional Variation: Add 1/2 cup chopped dates or ½ cup plus ı\ntablespoon of rose water to the dough for a floral twist.\nThese puffs freeze exceptionally well - simply reheat nto a\n225°C/435-VI0 oven for 8-10 minutes.\n\n---\n\nSPINACH AND RICOTTA PIE\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 lb fresh spinach (or 1 lb frozen, thawed)\n- 1½ cups whole milk ricotta cheese\n- ¾ cup finely grated Parmigiano-Reggiano\n- 3 large eggs\n- ¼ teaspoon freshly grated nutmeg\n- Salt and cracked black pepper to taste\n- 2 sheets thawed puff pastry\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n\nPreparation:\n1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C)\n2. Blanch spinach and squeeze completely dry\n3. Chop spinach finely and combine with ricotta, Parm, eggs\n4. Season generously with nutmeg, salt, pepper\n5. Layer puff pastry in 9-inch pan, add filling\n6. Top with second pastry sheet\n7. Bake 40-45 minutes until golden brown\n8. Let cool 10 minutes before slicing\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":75263,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens