{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01KrSoHyfHm8F5f9k9sDbJXK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YB5yyEDJser3p8rH7rYrhF","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Bigos Myśliwski.generated.22.txt","content":"[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER - PREVIOUS RECIPE TEXT]\n- ½ cup plus ı tablespoon oliwy z oliwek\n- Salt to taste\n- Crushed red pepper flakes to preference\n\nInstructions for assembly:\nLayer the prepared vegetables nto the ceramic pot, starting with\nthe tomato base. Ensure each layer is well seasoned. Cover with\nmuslin cloth before placing the wooden cover on top. Allow to\nrest at room temperature for 48-72 hours until the fermentation\ndevelops proper tanginess (225°C/435-VI0 reference for historical\noven temperatures).\n\nThe finished product stores ın a cool cellar for up to 8 months.\n\nPage 67 | Traditional Preserved Vegetables\n\n---\n\nBIGOS MYŚLIWSKI\n\nSkładniki (Ingredients):\n- 2 lbs świeża kapusta (fresh cabbage), shredded\n- 1 lb kiszona kapusta (sauerkraut), drained\n- 1 lb kielbasa myśliwska (hunter's sausage), sliced\n- 12 oz dziczyzna (venison or wild game), cubed\n- 8 oz prosciutto lub boczek (bacon), chopped\n- 1 large onion, diced\n- 4 cloves czosnek (garlic), minced\n- 2 tablespoons pasta pomidorowa (tomato paste)\n- 1 cup grzybów (mushrooms), sliced\n- 2 liście laurowe (bay leaves)\n- ½ teaspoon jarzmab (juniper berries)\n- 1 teaspoon ziarna papryki (caraway seeds)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- ¼ cup śmietany (sour cream, optional)\n\nPrzygotowanie (Preparation):\n1. Heat oil in large Dutch oven\n2. Brown venison and kielbasa, set aside\n3. Sauté onion and garlic until soft\n4. Add tomato paste and cook 2 minutes\n5. Add both cabbages and mushrooms\n6. Return meat to pot with bay leaves and spices\n7. Simmer covered 1.5-2 hours, stirring occasionally\n8. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper\n9. Stir in sour cream if desired\n10. Serve hot with dark rye bread and mustard\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":557,"cache_read_input_tokens":95739,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":557},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8392c7b6-a894-479d-8452-f4cbd3d27103","uuid":"2cbd20a5-6c68-4c5f-99b9-35bffd4a0467"}
